        "press": [{
          "id": "0",
          "title": "Facebook can now replace your weather app",
          "publisher": "TechCrunch",
          "url": "http://techcrunch.com/2017/02/08/facebook-can-now-replace-your-weather-app/"
        }, {
          "id": "1",
          "title": "Facebook now has a built-in weather app",
          "publisher": "Mashable",
          "url": "http://mashable.com/2017/02/09/facebook-weather/"
        }, {
          "id": "3",
          "title": "Now Facebook wants to be your weather app",
          "publisher": "Fast Company",
          "url": "https://news.fastcompany.com/now-facebook-wants-to-be-your-weather-app-4030534"
        }],
        "modules": [{
          "type": "module-text",
          "props": {
            "title": "Can we make weather forecasts more permanent and deterministic?",
            "subtitle": "The problem"
          },
          "children": [{
            "type": "text",
            "children": "During my first internship at Facebook, I worked to create a home for weather on iOS and Android."
          }, {
            "type": "text",
            "children": "Previously, people could weather on a promotional unit in the news feed, but this system was not permanent and did not provide enough information."
          }, {
            "type": "text",
            "children": "I introduced a system for detailed weather information that people can access every day, whenever they want. My final deliverable was a permanent home for weather that people can refer back to whenever needed."
          }]
        }, {
          "type": "module-media-full-width",
          "children": [{
            "type": "video",
            "props": {
              "title": "Prototype 1",
              "src": "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/folkloric-house-95904.appspot.com/o/160616%2FMaster.mov?alt=media&token=6675f33f-2903-480e-9007-be674b2f5127",
              "alt": "A prototype for the weather permalink."
            }
          }]
        }, {
          "type": "module-text",
          "props": {
            "title": "Find the Design Language for Weather",
            "subtitle": "Empathize with users and audit existing solutions"
          },
          "children": [{
            "type": "text",
            "children": "The project started with identifying user tasks and researching current solutions. I believe it is difficult to design a successful product without first understanding the user and understanding existing solutions. At the end of the project, a product is a designed solution to some problem people encounter. Understanding people helps the designer create the first solutions. In most cases, other designers have created their own solutions to the problem."
          }, {
            "type": "text",
            "children": "Externally, I audited most existing weather applications for both Android and iOS. Interally, on Facebook, I searched for existing patterns I could follow as I designed this weather system."
          }]
        }, {
          "type": "module-media-full-width",
          "children": [{
            "type": "image",
            "props": {
              "src": "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/folkloric-house-95904.appspot.com/o/160616%2Faudit.png?alt=media&token=c834be76-ec93-4833-82af-294728b004d1"
            }
          }]
        }, {
          "type": "module-text",
          "props": {
            "title": "Design the Best Solution",
            "subtitle": "Explore and prototype multiple directions"
          },
          "children": [{
            "type": "text",
            "children": "I explored three unique directions for this product. The first direction focuses on a data-first experience. In this direction, numeric information, like current, high, and low temperatures, is highest in the hierarchy."
          }, {
            "type": "text",
            "children": "More unique to Facebook, the second direction emphasizes a social component. The design establishes the weather with a personalized greeting and an activity suggestion. The same numeric information as the first direction is present, but lower in the hierarchy."
          }, {
            "type": "text",
            "children": "The third direction is a hybrid of the social and utility directions. In this direction, I show the numeric information first, but also include the social component, making the product unique to Facebook, while also useful."
          }]
        }, {
          "type": "module-media",
          "props": {
            "caption": "Utility Direction"
          },
          "children": [{
